      "id": "PopularPost114302",
      "post_content": "Wow this guy seems annoying, for both players.   \nMakes me want to break it though.  \n  \nUsing cards that all ready have phasing makes sense so [Teferi's Isle](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teferi's Isle) seems a good start. [Shimmering efreet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shimmering efreet) can stall, [Teferi's imp](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teferi's imp) can loot for you for free. [Time and tide](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Time and tide) can let you keep some control of things. [Teferi's realm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teferi's realm) keeps things fair sort of. ([Teferi](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teferi), was the guy that invented phasing by the way.) [Taniwha](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Taniwha) seems like a great finisher and with no down side since everything is phasing anyway. [Evacuation](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Evacuation) would be hilariously good for you if most of your guys are phased out when you do it, that would really help stall or clear the way. Also, it's twin [Sunder](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sunder) will greatly even the field, instead of having twice as many lands as you, they just won't have any and you still have your other half. If pairing w... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
